    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="320"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10793.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Minister for Foreign Affairs of Guatemala</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your polite communication of the 30th of November last, by which you
                    inform this department that the Interoceanic Railway of Guatemala will be
                    formally opened on the 15th of the present month, and are so good as to invite
                    representation by the United States at the ceremonies.</p>
                <p>In reply I am happy to inform your excellency that the President has been pleased
                    to select Maj. Gen. George W. Davis, United States Army, retired, to represent
                    the United States on this occasion.</p>
                <p>I congratulate your excellency on the completion and inauguration of this
                    enterprise, which will so materially add to the development and growth of the
                    resources and industries of Guatemala.</p>
                <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
